Executive Profile
Donald T. Grimes  Chief Financial Officer, Chief Operations Officer and Senior Vice President, Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 0 Board Members in 0 different organizations across 9 different industries.55--
Background

		Mr. Donald T. Grimes, also known as Don, has been Chief Financial Officer, Chief Operations Officer and Senior Vice President at Sally Beauty Holdings, Inc., since December 12, 2016. Mr. Grimes serves as Managing Director of mytheresa.com GmbH. Mr. Grimes serves as the Principal Financial & Accounting Officer, Vice President and Treasurer at Open Water Ventures, LLC. Mr. Grimes served as the Chief Financial Officer, Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President ... at Neiman Marcus Group LTD LLC from June 15, 2015 to November 14, 2016. He served as the Chief Financial Officer, Chief Operating Officer and Executive Vice President at The Neiman Marcus Group, LLC since June 15, 2016. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Chief Operating Officer at Neiman Marcus Group, Inc. since June 15, 2016 until November 14, 2016 and served as its Executive Vice President since June 15, 2016. He served as the Chief Financial Officer, Chief Accounting Officer, Treasurer and Senior Vice President at Wolverine World Wide Inc. from May 27, 2008 to June 12, 2015. He served as the Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Keystone Automotive Holdings, Inc. He served as Chief Financial Officer and Executive Vice President of Keystone Automotive Operations Inc. from January 22, 2007 to May 23, 2008 and served as its Principal Accounting Officer. He joined Keystone after a successful 15-year career at Brown-Forman Corporation. He served as Vice President of Beverage Finance, Director of Beverage Finance responsible for all finance activities of Brown-Forman. He served as Director of Corporate Planning and Analysis of Brown-Forman Corporation since August 12, 2003 and served as its Vice President of Corporate Development. He was responsible for forecasting and planning activities for both Brown Forman Corp. and Brown-Forman Beverages, Brown Forman Corp.'s largest subsidiary. He also oversaw investor relations, Brown Forman Corp.'s resource allocation process and the brand business analysis function. He joined Brown-Forman in 1991 and has served in a variety of important financial roles. He served as the Chief Financial Officer of Brown-Forman Spirits Americas. He started his career and served as a Certified Public Accountant of Coopers & Lybrand (now PwC). Mr. Grimes holds a Bachelor of Science degree from the University of Louisville in Louisville, Kentucky and a Master's in Business Administration from the J.L. Kellogg Graduate School of Management at Northwestern University in Evanston, Illinois.Read Full Background




